parameters.name: Asc
parameters.description:
The running sequence of task flows for data backfill. Valid values:

*   **0**: reverse chronological order.
*   **1**: chronological order. This is the default value.

parameters.name: BackFillDate
parameters.description: The date for the data to be backfilled. This parameter is required if you specify a date for data backfill.

parameters.name: BackFillDateBegin
parameters.description: The start date of the date range for the data to be backfilled. This parameter is required if you specify a date range for data backfill.

parameters.name: BackFillDateEnd
parameters.description: The end date of the date range for the data to be backfilled. This parameter is required if you specify a date range for data backfill.

parameters.name: DagId
parameters.description: The ID of the task flow. You can call the [ListTaskFlow](~~424565~~) or [ListLhTaskFlowAndScenario](~~426672~~) operation to query the task flow ID.

parameters.name: FilterNodeIds
parameters.description: Filter condition, which specifies the list of node IDs in the task flow that do not need to supplement data.

parameters.name: HistoryDagId
parameters.description: The ID of the historical task flow.

parameters.name: Interval
parameters.description: The interval at which data backfill is performed. Unit: hours. Minimum value: 1. Default value: 24.

parameters.name: IsTriggerSubTree
parameters.description: Specifies whether to run descendant nodes. Default value: true.

parameters.name: StartNodeIds
parameters.description: The number of nodes for which you want to backfill data.

parameters.name: Tid
parameters.description:
The ID of the tenant.

>  To view the ID of the tenant, go to the Data Management (DMS) console and move the pointer over the profile picture in the upper-right corner. For more information, see [View information about the current tenant](~~181330~~).
